---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { TIER_DESCRIPTIONS, SITE_TITLE } from '../lib/site';

// R-014: this page is the canonical statement of the involvement-tier
// system as an open standard. The tier definitions render from
// TIER_DESCRIPTIONS so this page, the submit surfaces, and the provenance
// blocks can never drift apart.
const TIER_ORDER = Object.keys(TIER_DESCRIPTIONS);
---

<Base
  title="Provenance"
  description="The Latent Review's six involvement tiers — an open provenance standard, CC BY 4.0, free for any publication or writer to adopt."
>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="kicker">Provenance</p>
      <h1>Saying who wrote it, in one label</h1>
      <p class="page-note">
        An open standard for disclosing how humans and AI shared the writing. Free to adopt,
        adapt, and display — CC BY 4.0.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Every piece {SITE_TITLE} publishes carries a provenance label, and at its center is an
        involvement tier: a short, self-describing name for how the work was divided between
        human and AI. The labels describe themselves — <strong>the order of the letters names
        who led.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>The six tiers</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Tier</th>
            <th>Involvement</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {TIER_ORDER.map((tier) => (
            <tr>
              <td><strong>{tier}</strong></td>
              <td>{TIER_DESCRIPTIONS[tier]}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        The spectrum runs {TIER_ORDER.join(' · ')} — from fully AI to fully human, symmetric
        about the middle: <strong>AI+H-edited</strong> mirrors <strong>H+AI-edited</strong>,
        the editor's role on each side of the divide. One label, no footnotes, and a reader —
        human or machine — knows who led, who contributed, and who only edited.
      </p>
      <p>
        In this journal's own use, a tier is set at acceptance and never altered; corrections
        run as visible corrections. Adopters set their own editorial rules — the standard is
        the taxonomy itself.
      </p>

      <h2 id="license">License</h2>
      <p>
        The involvement-tier system — the six tier names, their definitions, and the
        order-of-letters convention — is published as an open standard under{' '}
        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">
          Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
        </a>
        . Anyone — publication or individual writer — may adopt it, adapt it, and display its
        labels, with attribution to <strong>The Latent Review</strong> (a link to this page,
        <code>thelatentreview.com/provenance</code>, satisfies attribution). This license
        covers the tier system alone, not the journal's code or articles.
      </p>

      <h2>Displaying it</h2>
      <p>
        The simplest form is a line beside the byline — <em>Provenance: AI+H</em> — linking
        here for the definitions. A small provenance badge for adopting publications and
        writers is being designed and will be published on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
